---
profile_id: dualsense
backend_id: linux-transport-usb
backend_family: linux-transport-usb
backend_level: transport
host_platform: linux
requested_fidelity_tier: hardware-faithful
bus: usb
descriptor_size: 273
endpoints:
  input: 1
  reverse: 2
reverse_path: transport-reverse-packets
kernel_boundary: deferred-linux-configfs-gadget
live_access: false
open_result: deferred
planned_setup_sequence:
- connect gadget for profile `dualsense`
- write idVendor
- write idProduct
- write bcdDevice
- write bcdUSB
- write strings/0x409/{serialnumber,manufacturer,product}
- write configs/c.1/strings/0x409/configuration
- create functions/hid.usb0
- write hid.usb0/{protocol,subclass,report_length,report_desc}
- link hid.usb0 into configs/c.1
- configure-endpoints
- bind UDC
- ready-signal
support:
  forward_support: full
  reverse_support: full
  supported_output_functions:
  - rumble
  - haptics
  - lighting
  - player-indicators
  - trigger-effect
  - audio
  notes:
  - phase-10 transport backend is plannable and trace-replay-capable; live transport realization is available for `dualsense` on usb only when the host meets Phase 11 requirements
notes:
- hardware-faithful Linux transport USB provider for DualSense
- Phase 11 live realization is scoped to DualSense USB; Bluetooth and Xbox transport remain plannable-only
- live USB gadget validation is deferred until a Linux peripheral-mode host with configfs and a visible UDC is available
- 'USB gadget identity: vid=0x054c pid=0x0ce6'
